name: Hotel Sentral
address: Jl. A. Yani No.48, Kaliuntu, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81114, Indonesia
review 1: very suitable for families with spacious rooms to get extraordinary service and the most comfortable place to relax
review 2:
It‚Äôs an old hotel, it could be clean though. We took one of the VIP rooms I believe. We got AC, shower, small bars of soap n towels but not hot water. Bathroom was dirty, the sink too.
It‚Äôs pandemic, no tourism, less staff probably. We just walked in, no reservation. Had we made one, they‚Äôd probably prep/clean the room. The twin beds were very comfy. N the staff were polite n helpful.
review 3:
Worst hotel in Bali I have been to, I've chosen the viproom for 200.000. Man can i tell you that in this place VIP means go f yourself.

Bed sheets were not included, yes we were sleeping on a bed with no sheets at all!!! The room was dirty and the best thing is people were sitting in front of our room talking till 2 am. Requested the staff to say and do something about it but they were like ah what can i do about it.

Had almost no sleep, since at 6 am people started to talk again in front of the room.

So besides it being dirty expensive and managed by a baboon  you have a better change in sleeping in your car along the road then staying at this place.
review 4: This hotel is pretty nice and located strategically in the city of Singaraja. It takes around 15-20 minutes to reach Penimbangan or Lovina Beach. The price is reasonable 110k/nite on direct booking (I got 110.700 from Agoda) for room with fan (include breakfast). We found some bad points for their cleanliness, no blanket, no toiletries, even facility of wifi that we supposedly got from app booking, was not working. When I asked for wifi password to the front desk staff, she said the connection couldn't reach the backside (we got room at the back in this period). Hopefully, the property will improve their facilities for better convenience of the guests who are staying here. However, this place is still recommended to be your option  as overnight stay when you are visiting North Bali or as another option for having rest before leaving to Denpasar.
review 5: Good place for transit hotel , clean room , staff very helping

name: Rumah Makan Gandi
address: Jl. A. Yani No.25H, Kp. Anyar, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81114, Indonesia
review 1: Great food by the 2 of us in our group. I got the fried pigeon, something new I wanted to try. It was good, even with the entire head still attached! Good food and service was good. They bring you a paper and you write your own order, kinda different idea but I liked it. The Soda Gambira (happy soda) they do there are the best I've had.
review 2: Gandi is one of legendary chinesse food restaurant in Singaraja, otherwisw they serve Indonesian food in the the whole Singaraja and Lovina area. All food is delicious and the service is swift and pleasant.  Chinese food and local Indonesian and Western food. The Wanton soup, the Japanese Tofu and vegetables, Their kwetaiw noodles and all of the freshly made fruit juices..
review 3:
Location is slightly hidden from the street, check google map.
The place is a bit small with few tables, so can be rly crowded.
Specializing in chinese food, we ordered pork n vegi dishes ; imho, quite good, or even delicious for bali std.
Pricewise, I'd say quite cheap, with majority of meat dishes below idr50K.
We visited in apr 2021 and still quite crowded, so avoid lunch hour.
review 4: Old style chinese food, which is worth to try. Strategically located in town. Koloke, nasi goreng, the best üëå
review 5: Fantastic food in downtown of Singaraja.  Good taste , a lot of menu and choices ,  it's really good food even if you compare with Denpasar. The interior is 70' design and decoration. Located inside the Ruko complex.  Must visit restaurant when you are in Singaraja.

name: Gelato Corner Cafe
address: Jl. Udayana No.11A, Banjar Jawa, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81114, Indonesia
review 1:
It's Thursday and very quiet. Likely won't be like this weekends.
Gelato is great, good selection and variety.
Reasonable price considering Bali is a tourist destination with tourists prices.
review 2:
The only best gelato In Nort Bali.

love it. Many choice
review 3: BEST ICE CREAM/ GELATO IN TOWN/WHOLE BALI seriously. They staffs are friendly that one day we came too late they were closing but they let us order last minute. Price is acceptable. Thanks for the advancement of availability in north bali! Keep it up
review 4:
We stumbled upon this place by accident. Our hotel was in Ubud and we just visited Banyumala twin waterfall. We thought we drove down to Singaraja to get a coffee.

We weren't sure if there's any open since it is a new year day, Jan 1st. Our first choice coffee house was close so the next closest to our location was this place. We googled everything through Google maps. To our surprise this place was not only open but also serve good coffee, ice cream with many many interesting flavours and delicious.

Their banana chocolate ice was good. They also had black diamond, it is charcoal with vanilla.... It was delicious. Sadly I didn't get to take shot of the ice cream.

We also had our dinner there and everything was delicious. The staff was friendly and warm as well.

It was sure a long drive since we drove back through Kintamani to Ubud, it was late and the fog had come down. But it was one of the best road trip with many delicious surprises. We will definitely drive there again to enjoy their food.
review 5: Great new Place with home made italian Ice Cream. If you happen to Visit Singaraja, it's a must to come over and enjoy the ambiance with a great taste of Ice Cream. 2 thumbs up üëçüëç

address: Depan GOR Bhuana Patra, Jl. Udayana No.8, Banjar Jawa, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81114, Indonesia
types: italian_restaurant, pizza_restaurant, wholesaler, restaurant, food, store
review 1:
This is definetely the place to be if you crave a good plate of pasta as it should be whilst in Bali. They do the pasta fresh for every order. I watched them doing it whilst sneaking a peak (or two) behind the kitchen glass window. Then, it is cooked to perfection aldente and dressed with a lovely sauce of your choice. The fresh basil pesto tastes so good and homemade that we had to come back all the way from Lovina the next day for it! We also ordered a side salad and the ingredients were fresh and crispy dressed in a well seasoned, tasty dressing. The pizza crust is also thin and good. But the pasta is just superb. The service people are really kind and attentive. üôè
The atmosphere is not that appealing as it is right on a busy road but we did not care for this as the food is so good and the servers did a lovely job.
Recommended pasta type: pasta rigatoni are the best.
review 2: A very good restaurant.  It is incredibly clean and they serve good quality Italian food for local prices.  Really recommended.
review 3: FANTASTIC FOOD, FANTASTIC SERVICE. We went to this small restaurant for pizza and was surprised to find the best Italian food we have had anywhere let alone here in Bali. Everything is fresh and made on site you can taste the difference (I challange Gordon Ramsey to trying this food im certain he could not do better). If you are in the area check it out because the food, service  atmosphere and price are perfect.
review 4: Fettucine flavour is subtle, gentle and smooth, a perfect balance of spiciness from cracked pepper, aromatique from herbs and garlic. On the other hand, rigatoni flavour would be a gentle tangy and heat with nice smoky aroma from it‚Äôs smoked salmon that mixed into restaurant signature sauce. The quantity of both   Food will make you full to the brim for one person
review 5: One of best pizza and pasta.. the owner is Victor, a real Chef.... the pesto is perfect
